{% if render_mode == "transform" or render_mode == "full" or render_mode == "thoughts" %}
{# SeversHearth — Camp Awareness ────────────────────────────────────────
   Injects ongoing camp context into a follower's character_bio block.
   While a camp is active and this actor is a tracked follower, every
   dialogue line from them is rendered with the camp summary appended,
   so the LLM naturally references "the camp" / "this place" / "tonight"
   without us having to fire a one-shot event.

   Decorator: `current_camp(actorUUID)` — registered by SeversHearthNative
   in SkyrimNetBridge.h. Returns "The player has a camp pitched near
   <location>, established <N minutes|hours|days> ago." while a camp is
   active in CampStore; empty string otherwise. The empty-string return
   makes the {% if camp_ctx %} guard work cleanly without a separate
   IsActive query.

   Gating: only fires for followers (`is_follower` || `is_sever_follower`)
   so random villagers / Whiterun guards don't reference the player's
   wilderness camp in their dialogue.

   Note: the render_mode check is intentionally on line 1 so SkyrimNet's
   prompt linter can early-skip without parsing the comment — keeps the
   "render_mode check in first 5 lines" best-practice happy. ─────────#}
{% if actorUUID and actorUUID != 0 %}
{% set is_fol = is_follower(actorUUID) or is_sever_follower(actorUUID) %}
{% if is_fol %}
{% set camp_ctx = current_camp(actorUUID) %}
{% if camp_ctx and camp_ctx != "" %}
{{ camp_ctx }}

You and the player share this camp. Treat it as a known waypoint you can reference naturally — you might suggest resting here, mention a shared meal or the fire's warmth, or comment on the place. Do not invent specific furnishings or details about who built what — only what would be plain to anyone sitting around the fire. Let camp references come up organically when they fit the conversation; don't volunteer them unprompted.
{% endif %}
{% endif %}
{% endif %}
{% endif %}
